South African Democratic Teachers Union (Sadtu) is going to court on Monday to challenge the re-writing of matric exams. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Democratic Teachers Union (Sadtu) is going to fight the rewriting of matric exams in court. The union says it will be filing court papers on Monday, to challenge the decision by the Basic Education Department. The scheduled rewrite follows leaks of two papers. Sadtu has labelled the decision irrational. Watch the video above for more details. 